feat(ops): realtime-UX Grafana dashboard + SLO burn-rate alerts

- deploy/grafana/t2a-realtime-ux.json: self-contained dashboard with
  five SLO stat panels (30-day rolling) at the top, followed by
  drill-downs for click_to_confirmed, SSE fanout (publish/resync/drop,
  subscriber lag p50/p99, active subscribers, RUM-side reconnect &
  resync), optimistic rollback per kind, and Web Vitals. All queries
  parameterised on ${DS_PROMETHEUS}; thresholds match docs/SLOs.md.
- deploy/prometheus/t2a-taskapi-rules.yaml: add SLI recording rules
  (taskapi:rum:click_to_confirmed_p95_seconds, taskapi:sse:resync_rate5m,
  taskapi:sse:subscriber_lag_p99_seconds, taskapi:rum:optimistic_
  rollback_rate5m, taskapi:rum:mutation_error_rate5m) and multi-window
  multi-burn-rate alerts (fast = 1h/14.4x, slow = 6h/6x) for each of the
  five SLOs from docs/SLOs.md. Labels include slo= and burn_rate= so the
  Alertmanager routing tree can page vs ticket without reparsing the
  name.
- deploy/grafana/README.md + deploy/prometheus/README.md updated to
  cross-link the dashboard and rule file, with a reminder to keep the
  thresholds in those two files and docs/SLOs.md in sync.
